        "Description/Abstract": "An extensive amount of research has established the efficacy of using linguistic-based cues to detect deception.  It has been previously shown that many deception detection methods are vulnerable to countermeasures, though the use of countermeasures to change or suppress linguistic-based cues to deception has not been investigated. In this study, we will empirically examine whether deceivers trained in linguistic-based cues are able to avoid to detection during an online chat with another person.  This manuscript is under development with data collection tentatively planned for Fall 2018. ",
